the illegal immigration problem was started by continued and made worse by government 100 years ago we had free and open borders to the south and supply and demand for labor determined how many came
If you are talking about the United States, between 1820 and 1920, the population more than quadrupled, from about 9 to 39 million. In that same time, the number of immigrants coming to the US increased from about 30,000 per year to 1.3 million per year. It seems that, at least in that time frame, "government" didn't do much about it.
